Policy 3: ATTACKER_TO_WAN
Purpose:
Allows Attacker VM internet access for:
• Downloading malware samples (safe lab)
• Updating tools
• Launching outbound scans
Key Configuration:
• Incoming: ATTACKER (port3)
• Outgoing: WAN (port1)
• Source: Attacker-subnet
• Destination: all
• Service: ALL
• NAT: ON (PAT to WAN IP)
What logs appear?
• Web Filter logs (if attacker VM opens URLs)
• IPS logs (if attacker tries malicious outbound traffic)
• DNS logs (resolver queries)
